title: For Sale:  Flintlock Brown Bess New England Militia Musket ANTIQUE Massachusetts Fullstock Military .75 Cal
postcontent: Brown Bess Inspired Flintlock Massachusetts (aka "New England") Militia Musket, .75 cal smoothbore, mfg. ca. 1820's. These "New England" or "Massachusetts" militia muskets were built to be dual purpose arms to serve minutemen both at home and on the field. Their design shares attributes from standard military muskets of the day as well as civilian fowling pieces. This example was constructed with the Brown Bess pattern in mind and even utilizes several resourced Brown Bess parts. The barrel measures 38 1/2" long and may have started life on a Brown Bess. It is unmarked and features a small dovetailed brass blade front sight with a bayonet lug mounted under the muzzle. The engraved lock is a trade piece marked "SAMUEL MOORE / WARRANTED". Overall the metal has a very pleasing dark plum patina. The stock features a slight flare just behind the ramrod entry pipe which is distinctive of a Brown Bess. The wood has an attractive, dark untouched patina overall with surprisingly no chips, cracks, or repairs whatsoever. A thin coat of varnish has been added long ago, much of which has since worn away. Brass buttplate, lock screw escutcheons, triggerguard, and ramrod pipes all retain a dark mellowed patina. The pipes are no doubt taken from a Brown Bess. The very tip of the entry pipe is broken away. Original iron ramrod appears to be blacksmith made. The action is crisp and functions perfectly while the frizzen snaps shut and springs forward securely. This is a fantastic example of a scarce Brown Bess inspired militia musket. No FFL required on pre-1899 firearms or contemporary muzzleloaders.fedex, ups  Shipping cost $30.
